1
00:00:46,750 --> 00:00:50,840
<i>That despicable little smirk on his face.</i>

2
00:00:54,840 --> 00:00:57,180
<i>That dreadful laugh...</i>

3
00:00:57,260 --> 00:00:59,260
<i>with his cheeks</i>
<i>contorting slightly upwards.</i>

4
00:01:13,610 --> 00:01:19,910
<i>He didn't look anything</i>
<i>like a Nazi SS officer.</i>

5
00:01:21,580 --> 00:01:27,710
But at the time, in 1941, you all...

6
00:01:27,960 --> 00:01:30,040
The Vatican's
European General Directorate...

7
00:01:30,130 --> 00:01:33,460
collaborated with him
and his organization.

8
00:01:34,420 --> 00:01:36,930
We were forced to collaborate.

9
00:01:37,010 --> 00:01:40,720
He was carrying a direct
order from the<i></i>Führer.

10
00:01:41,810 --> 00:01:43,850
Yes, of course.

11
00:01:45,600 --> 00:01:48,520
And they commenced operations.

12
00:01:51,730 --> 00:01:58,320
<i>The operation and their scheme are</i>
<i>ingrained in my memory, my Master.</i>

13
00:01:58,410 --> 00:01:59,740
<i>Well done.</i>

14
00:01:59,870 --> 00:02:03,830
<i>Arucard, Her Majesty herself is</i>
<i>convening a round table discussion.</i>

15
00:02:03,910 --> 00:02:06,960
<i>Oh, the Queen?</i>

16
00:02:07,040 --> 00:02:11,670
Return at once and report the details.
Don't keep her waiting.

17
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:14,000
Yes.

18
00:02:14,630 --> 00:02:18,550
Did you enjoy the thrill of war, Integra?

19
00:02:19,590 --> 00:02:21,390
Did you feel the blood rush down there?

20
00:02:21,890 --> 00:02:25,060
Did you see the dark red flame?

21
00:02:25,140 --> 00:02:28,140
Shut up, you idiot! Who gives a damn!

22
00:02:28,230 --> 00:02:30,350
Now get back here, damn you!

23
00:02:39,950 --> 00:02:43,330
What the hell are you people doing?

24
00:02:43,410 --> 00:02:47,500
There's absolutely no way
I can tell you that, Colonel.

25
00:02:47,580 --> 00:02:51,170
It's a top secret order
issued by the late Führer.

26
00:02:58,760 --> 00:03:01,300
Get off your high horse!

27
00:03:01,510 --> 00:03:04,600
Why won't you turn us into vampires?!

28
00:03:04,680 --> 00:03:09,390
Why? Why?! Answer me, you bastard!

29
00:03:11,190 --> 00:03:14,560
That's enough, Colonel.

30
00:03:15,190 --> 00:03:18,780
Any more of this childish behavior
and I'll blow your head off.

31
00:03:25,410 --> 00:03:29,580
What are you doing?

32
00:03:29,830 --> 00:03:35,090
What do you intend to do with
your army of 1000 vampires?

33
00:03:35,380 --> 00:03:36,710
Major?!

34
00:03:37,920 --> 00:03:41,300
<i>The pudgy little man</i>
<i>with the glasses said it...</i>

35
00:03:41,510 --> 00:03:45,180
<i>as if he were hell's</i>
<i>own commanding officer.</i>

36
00:03:47,970 --> 00:03:52,060
I intend to savor
the infinite pleasures of war.

37
00:03:52,940 --> 00:03:55,730
Of the next war...

38
00:03:55,810 --> 00:03:58,730
and the next war after that one.

39
00:04:01,780 --> 00:04:06,870
The operation
called for creating vampires...

40
00:04:07,160 --> 00:04:09,620
the secret "Last Battalion."

41
00:04:10,040 --> 00:04:11,370
It's simple.

42
00:04:11,830 --> 00:04:16,130
You helped fund the operation.

43
00:04:16,960 --> 00:04:19,300
And you knew about it as well.

44
00:04:19,500 --> 00:04:21,130
You knowingly collaborated.

45
00:04:22,590 --> 00:04:26,260
Forced to? Nonsense.

46
00:04:26,600 --> 00:04:28,970
You wanted him to turn you into a vampire.

47
00:04:30,020 --> 00:04:31,770
It wasn't just me!

48
00:04:31,850 --> 00:04:34,020
All of us were...

49
00:04:34,100 --> 00:04:36,350
They tricked me...

50
00:04:36,440 --> 00:04:37,980
Help me...

51
00:04:38,400 --> 00:04:40,570
Please, Maxwell.

52
00:04:40,940 --> 00:04:42,440
I'm begging you!

53
00:04:42,860 --> 00:04:43,860
Nope.

54
00:04:43,950 --> 00:04:45,240
SLURP

55
00:04:45,990 --> 00:04:48,830
Can't do it.
It's impossible to get back.

56
00:04:48,910 --> 00:04:51,830
It'll take an extra week by boat.

57
00:04:52,080 --> 00:04:53,960
An airplane is out of the question.

58
00:04:54,040 --> 00:04:57,040
We can't leave that
big wooden box here, can we?

59
00:05:03,550 --> 00:05:06,260
This is my final domain.

60
00:05:06,680 --> 00:05:09,760
This is where I was born
and this is where I will die.

61
00:05:09,850 --> 00:05:12,310
SLURP SLURP

62
00:05:38,210 --> 00:05:41,420
So you want some more, Anderson?!

63
00:05:44,010 --> 00:05:46,220
Arucard!

64
00:06:10,780 --> 00:06:16,250
The Vatican has a small jet airplane
13 kilometers north of here.

65
00:06:16,750 --> 00:06:19,750
Take that release paper
and get the hell out of here...

66
00:06:20,290 --> 00:06:24,500
before I decide to kill you again.

67
00:06:34,010 --> 00:06:35,430
Amen.

68
00:07:31,240 --> 00:07:34,450
I'm back, my Master.

69
00:07:35,200 --> 00:07:37,990
Job well done, my servant.

70
00:07:38,620 --> 00:07:42,080
You're in the presence of the Queen.
Take off your sunglasses.

71
00:08:09,280 --> 00:08:11,950
It's been a long time, Vampire.

72
00:08:12,450 --> 00:08:14,780
Let me get a closer look at you.

73
00:08:22,160 --> 00:08:26,130
You haven't changed at all, Arucard.

74
00:08:26,670 --> 00:08:30,710
You can see the years have
taken their toll on me.

75
00:08:31,090 --> 00:08:33,840
I'm a wrinkled old lady.

76
00:08:34,430 --> 00:08:39,350
You're still the same spirited girl
you were 50 years ago, my lady.

77
00:08:39,810 --> 00:08:45,350
No, your highness is without a doubt
even more beautiful today.

78
00:08:49,110 --> 00:08:52,110
Give me your report, Vampire.

79
00:08:56,070 --> 00:08:59,870
Fifty-five years ago,
a crazed Nazi major...

80
00:08:59,950 --> 00:09:03,120
attempted to create a vampire army.

81
00:09:16,380 --> 00:09:20,430
Walter and I laid waste to the operation.

82
00:09:20,970 --> 00:09:24,730
However, they refused to give up.

83
00:09:25,560 --> 00:09:28,860
Now they're trying to
complete their research.

84
00:09:29,150 --> 00:09:33,860
They're the remnants
of the Third Reich's...

85
00:09:34,400 --> 00:09:35,990
"Last Battalion."

86
00:09:36,070 --> 00:09:37,570
That's what Millennium is.

87
00:09:41,870 --> 00:09:44,830
Tubalcain's blood must have given us away.

88
00:09:46,290 --> 00:09:48,250
The Major really blew it.

89
00:09:51,130 --> 00:09:52,210
Hold it.

90
00:09:52,300 --> 00:09:55,720
I'm the messenger.
I'm not here to fight with you.

91
00:09:56,220 --> 00:09:57,470
Walter.

92
00:09:58,220 --> 00:10:02,220
Security was airtight.
And no sign of any breach.

93
00:10:03,430 --> 00:10:07,230
Your security is useless against me.
I'm everywhere and nowhere.

94
00:10:07,890 --> 00:10:09,520
He's only a child.

95
00:10:09,600 --> 00:10:12,770
What's Millennium? What are they after?

96
00:10:21,030 --> 00:10:22,280
What?

97
00:10:23,870 --> 00:10:25,410
Hello.

98
00:10:31,080 --> 00:10:32,500
Hello...

99
00:10:36,510 --> 00:10:40,260
To the representatives of Britain
and the Vatican who are here today...

100
00:10:40,340 --> 00:10:43,970
my commanding officer, the Major,
has something he wants to tell you.

101
00:10:44,060 --> 00:10:45,850
Please give him your attention.

102
00:10:47,230 --> 00:10:48,060
Huh?

103
00:10:48,980 --> 00:10:51,650
<i>What's the matter? There's no picture.</i>

104
00:10:51,730 --> 00:10:54,400
<i>Major, stop it!</i>
<i>For god's sake please don't.</i>

105
00:10:54,480 --> 00:10:58,110
<i>Warrant Officer Schrödinger,</i>
<i>the screen is completely blank.</i>

106
00:11:00,450 --> 00:11:06,080
<i>-Oh, I can see them now.</i>
<i>-Help! Please help!</i>

107
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:10,710
Major, it looks like you're having
quite a time over there.

108
00:11:11,370 --> 00:11:14,790
<i>No, a great weight has finally</i>
<i>been lifted from my shoulders.</i>

109
00:11:14,880 --> 00:11:18,460
<i>It feels good. It feels very good.</i>

110
00:11:18,550 --> 00:11:19,970
Hello, Major.

111
00:11:20,260 --> 00:11:23,090
<i>It's been a long time, Arucard.</i>

112
00:11:23,180 --> 00:11:25,720
<i>I'm extremely happy to see you again.</i>

113
00:11:28,980 --> 00:11:30,230
What is it you want?

114
00:11:32,770 --> 00:11:37,690
<i>It's the head of the Royal Order of</i>
<i>Religious Knights, Sir Integra Hellsing.</i>

115
00:11:37,780 --> 00:11:39,240
<i>It's a pleasure to meet you.</i>

116
00:11:39,610 --> 00:11:43,240
What is the purpose of this idiocy?

117
00:11:43,320 --> 00:11:44,450
Answer me!

118
00:11:45,200 --> 00:11:46,830
<i>The purpose?</i>

119
00:11:47,240 --> 00:11:52,500
<i>That's a stupid question,</i>
<i>my beautiful fräulein.</i>

120
00:11:54,250 --> 00:11:56,790
<i>Purpose? How funny.</i>

121
00:12:00,170 --> 00:12:03,300
To put it in the strongest terms,
fräulein...

122
00:12:03,470 --> 00:12:07,510
we have no purpose.

123
00:12:07,930 --> 00:12:09,850
HANG THE DEFEATIST!!

124
00:12:10,520 --> 00:12:13,100
You should know, fräulein...

125
00:12:13,310 --> 00:12:15,860
that there are those in this world,

126
00:12:15,940 --> 00:12:21,610
certain irredeemable louts,
for whom the means need no end.

127
00:12:25,450 --> 00:12:27,620
That is to say, ourselves.

128
00:12:32,660 --> 00:12:34,710
Don't stop until he is completely gone.

129
00:12:34,790 --> 00:12:39,130
We can't have him turning into a ghoul.

130
00:12:46,680 --> 00:12:52,480
Wow! That looks pretty harsh, Major.

131
00:12:52,560 --> 00:12:54,730
You people are insane.

132
00:12:55,020 --> 00:12:59,230
<i>Someone from the Vatican's Iscariot</i>
<i>Organization speaks of "insanity"?</i>

133
00:12:59,820 --> 00:13:04,610
<i>It is your God who guarantees my insanity.</i>

134
00:13:04,700 --> 00:13:07,240
<i>So let me ask you...</i>

135
00:13:09,240 --> 00:13:14,330
<i>Who is it that guarantees</i>
<i>your God's sanity?</i>

136
00:13:16,420 --> 00:13:19,960
<i>We are the Third Reich's SS.</i>

137
00:13:20,040 --> 00:13:23,300
<i>Do you have any idea how</i>
<i>many people we've killed?</i>

138
00:13:23,550 --> 00:13:26,970
We're insane?
As if it were something new.

139
00:13:27,050 --> 00:13:29,800
You should have said
that half a century ago.

140
00:13:30,050 --> 00:13:32,430
<i>Very well. Excellent.</i>

141
00:13:32,520 --> 00:13:36,980
<i>Then try to stop me,</i>
<i>you self-proclaimed "normal" people.</i>

142
00:13:37,060 --> 00:13:41,320
<i>But unfortunately,</i>
<i>you people are not my enemy.</i>

143
00:13:41,650 --> 00:13:44,190
<i>My enemy is Britain...</i>

144
00:13:44,400 --> 00:13:45,990
<i>Hellsing...</i>

145
00:13:46,070 --> 00:13:49,570
<i>No, it's that man</i>
<i>standing gleefully over there!</i>

146
00:14:04,050 --> 00:14:05,880
A splendid declaration of war.

147
00:14:06,220 --> 00:14:09,390
Fine. I'll annihilate you
as many times as I have to!

148
00:14:09,640 --> 00:14:12,390
<i>We will never give up.</i>

149
00:14:12,890 --> 00:14:16,890
<i>We'll reverse this ridiculous outcome</i>
<i>as many times as we have to.</i>

150
00:14:17,020 --> 00:14:19,150
Arucard, Seras. Shoot.

151
00:14:27,360 --> 00:14:31,570
<i>Shooting the messenger,</i>
<i>that's not very nice.</i>

152
00:14:32,120 --> 00:14:34,450
<i>Goodbye, fräulein.</i>

153
00:14:34,700 --> 00:14:37,830
<i>I look forward to meeting</i>
<i>again on the battlefield.</i>

154
00:14:54,060 --> 00:14:55,810
Sir Hellsing.

155
00:14:56,680 --> 00:14:58,060
Arucard.

156
00:15:03,150 --> 00:15:04,270
This is an order.

157
00:15:05,610 --> 00:15:08,030
Destroy them.

158
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:22,750
They're finally paying us some attention.

159
00:15:25,550 --> 00:15:32,050
Doc, Captain, once I start
to dance, I dance to the finish.

160
00:15:32,390 --> 00:15:35,220
Enjoy it as much as possible, right?

161
00:15:52,110 --> 00:15:53,700
You're slow!

162
00:15:53,780 --> 00:15:57,580
In the time it took you just
to walk down the hall,

163
00:15:57,660 --> 00:16:01,660
I went to London, got my head
blown off and made it back already.

164
00:16:02,080 --> 00:16:05,920
Perhaps you should go on a diet, Major.

165
00:16:08,130 --> 00:16:09,300
That's impossible.

166
00:16:10,880 --> 00:16:13,260
Warrant Officer Schrödinger,
stop being disrespectful.

167
00:16:13,630 --> 00:16:15,510
It's all right, Doctor.

168
00:16:15,600 --> 00:16:18,260
The Warrant Officer has
carried out his mission.

169
00:16:32,530 --> 00:16:34,320
Engage flaps!

170
00:16:42,080 --> 00:16:44,580
Commence Deus Ex Machina!

171
00:16:51,880 --> 00:16:56,180
This is the Last Battalion's Commander
speaking to the entire air fleet.

172
00:16:56,260 --> 00:16:59,890
We are headed for England's capital,
for the skies above London.

173
00:17:01,640 --> 00:17:03,600
Send up the beacon.

174
00:17:03,730 --> 00:17:06,770
The signal fire of defiance
announcing our return

175
00:17:06,850 --> 00:17:08,560
to this mortal world.

176
00:17:17,200 --> 00:17:21,370
<i>Let's sing a little song today</i>

177
00:17:21,870 --> 00:17:25,830
<i>And drink some cool wine</i>

178
00:17:26,670 --> 00:17:31,380
<i>The glasses should be ringing</i>

179
00:17:31,460 --> 00:17:35,420
<i>Since we must, we must part</i>

180
00:17:35,720 --> 00:17:40,350
<i>Give me your hand</i>

181
00:17:40,430 --> 00:17:44,600
<i>Your white hand</i>

182
00:17:44,680 --> 00:17:47,440
<i>Farewell, my love, farewell</i>

183
00:17:48,230 --> 00:17:54,860
<i>Farewell, farewell</i>

184
00:17:54,940 --> 00:17:58,820
<i>Since we're going</i>

185
00:17:59,700 --> 00:18:03,790
<i>Since we're going</i>

186
00:18:04,500 --> 00:18:11,130
<i>Since we're going against England</i>

187
00:18:11,630 --> 00:18:14,010
<i>England</i>

188
00:18:27,270 --> 00:18:30,100
And thus the ship came into my possession.

189
00:18:30,270 --> 00:18:32,520
Tinker, Tailor, Soldier, Sailor...

190
00:18:32,610 --> 00:18:35,480
My bullet punishes all
without distinction.

191
00:18:35,650 --> 00:18:37,610
Welcome aboard.

192
00:18:37,700 --> 00:18:39,990
You have your wish.

193
00:18:40,070 --> 00:18:42,450
We and our ship are
at Millennium's service.

194
00:18:42,830 --> 00:18:44,620
What's it like, new Captain?

195
00:18:44,700 --> 00:18:47,870
What's it like to become a vampire...

196
00:18:47,960 --> 00:18:52,340
after betraying your own country
and killing all your mates?

197
00:18:54,710 --> 00:18:55,630
I see.

198
00:18:56,510 --> 00:18:59,590
How does it feel to unleash
your powers of invincibility and...

199
00:18:59,680 --> 00:19:05,180
turn your superiors and subordinates
into ghoul corpses, new Captain?

200
00:19:08,560 --> 00:19:09,850
I see.

201
00:19:10,650 --> 00:19:14,190
Well done! This is amazing!

202
00:19:14,270 --> 00:19:16,980
Millennium is very happy to have you.

203
00:19:17,820 --> 00:19:20,240
Oh, you certainly deserve full credit.

204
00:19:20,950 --> 00:19:24,120
We couldn't have done it without you.

205
00:19:24,200 --> 00:19:27,750
The Major will be so happy.

206
00:19:29,330 --> 00:19:30,670
Well...

207
00:19:32,040 --> 00:19:36,300
now that the deed is done,
hurry up and die, Limey.

208
00:19:42,930 --> 00:19:43,970
You set us up, bitch!

209
00:19:45,350 --> 00:19:47,810
I only heard a single shot!

210
00:19:47,890 --> 00:19:50,310
But that's ridiculous! It can't be!

211
00:19:51,480 --> 00:19:55,020
I'm Rip Van Winkle, the hunter.

212
00:19:55,230 --> 00:19:57,320
Tinker, Tailor, Soldier, Sailor...

213
00:19:57,400 --> 00:19:59,490
My bullet punishes all
without distinction!

214
00:19:59,900 --> 00:20:01,450
You bitch!

215
00:20:03,740 --> 00:20:04,700
Foolish child.

216
00:20:32,020 --> 00:20:32,850
First Lieutenant.

217
00:20:32,940 --> 00:20:34,770
Oh, you're awake?

218
00:20:35,900 --> 00:20:39,780
I ran out of paint before I could finish,
but I guess this will do.

219
00:20:41,940 --> 00:20:46,620
We'd be a pretty sorry
looking ship without this.

220
00:20:48,030 --> 00:20:50,370
Our cursed banner.

221
00:20:52,500 --> 00:20:56,630
The German Third Reich's
Atlantic Fleet Flagship Adler...

222
00:20:57,420 --> 00:20:59,840
now commencing operations!

223
00:21:04,760 --> 00:21:07,140
No matter how many times we kill them,
they come back.

224
00:21:08,640 --> 00:21:11,270
They certainly are a persistent lot.

225
00:21:11,640 --> 00:21:15,770
However many times they come back,
we'll just keep killing them.

226
00:21:16,730 --> 00:21:18,560
It's as simple as that.

227
00:21:18,770 --> 00:21:22,280
This time it's not just the two of us.
We have a new member.

228
00:21:23,440 --> 00:21:26,240
There's something
I've been meaning to ask you.

229
00:21:26,320 --> 00:21:27,570
What?

230
00:21:27,990 --> 00:21:30,870
Why did you make Seras a vampire?

231
00:21:30,990 --> 00:21:36,080
Why would you of all people
do something so out of character?

232
00:21:37,210 --> 00:21:39,380
It was her decision.

233
00:21:39,460 --> 00:21:42,550
She chose her own path.

234
00:21:43,590 --> 00:21:45,340
What about her family?

235
00:21:45,720 --> 00:21:47,590
She doesn't have any. She's an orphan.

236
00:21:48,140 --> 00:21:50,350
I figured.

237
00:21:50,430 --> 00:21:54,850
She's much more interesting
than she looks.

238
00:21:55,480 --> 00:21:57,980
Her superiors and coworkers
were being turned

239
00:21:58,060 --> 00:22:00,690
into ghouls right and left
in her town of death.

240
00:22:00,770 --> 00:22:04,610
A vampire was trying to rape and kill her.

241
00:22:04,940 --> 00:22:07,740
It was a hell like the bottom
of a witch's cauldron.

242
00:22:07,820 --> 00:22:12,080
And what did she do?
What did she choose?

243
00:22:12,790 --> 00:22:15,370
Giving up is what kills people.

244
00:22:15,660 --> 00:22:22,590
Those who refuse to give up are
entitled to trample upon humanity.

245
00:22:24,800 --> 00:22:28,590
Now all she needs to
do is drink blood, right?

246
00:22:29,300 --> 00:22:31,850
She'll drink.

247
00:22:33,310 --> 00:22:35,060
She'll definitely drink.

248
00:23:04,040 --> 00:23:06,710
Why don't you drink blood?

249
00:23:07,590 --> 00:23:10,130
