to see panicked fresh recruits stabbing
dead enemy soldiers over and over again.

499
00:48:55,760 --> 00:48:58,890
The sight of despairing
deserters being strung up

500
00:48:58,970 --> 00:49:01,980
from a street lamp is
a pleasure I can't resist.

501
00:49:02,390 --> 00:49:05,520
There's nothing better than
lowering down my palm and

502
00:49:05,600 --> 00:49:09,480
seeing screaming prisoners
of war drop like flies

503
00:49:09,570 --> 00:49:13,150
as they're mowed down
by ear-piercing Schmeissers.

504
00:49:14,200 --> 00:49:19,450
When the pitiful resistance fighters
make their brave stand only to

505
00:49:19,870 --> 00:49:25,880
have their entire city smashed to
atoms by Dora's 4.8 ton bombshells...

506
00:49:25,960 --> 00:49:27,750
I'm simply in ecstasy!

507
00:49:28,590 --> 00:49:33,260
I like being ravaged by
Russian armored divisions.

508
00:49:33,670 --> 00:49:36,800
It's so sad to see towns that were
supposed to be defended at all costs

509
00:49:37,180 --> 00:49:39,050
being laid to waste...

510
00:49:39,140 --> 00:49:43,930
their women and children
being raped and killed.

511
00:49:44,350 --> 00:49:48,610
I like being squashed and exterminated
by Anglo-American material superiority.

512
00:49:49,230 --> 00:49:52,190
Crawling around on the ground like vermin

513
00:49:52,280 --> 00:49:55,610
while being hounded by
Jabos is the ultimate humiliation.

514
00:50:01,620 --> 00:50:05,330
My friends, I want war...

515
00:50:06,120 --> 00:50:09,000
Hellish war.

516
00:50:09,630 --> 00:50:10,750
My friends...

517
00:50:11,920 --> 00:50:16,010
My brothers in arms who serve me...

518
00:50:16,510 --> 00:50:18,680
What do you want?

519
00:50:19,260 --> 00:50:22,220
Do you want further war?

520
00:50:23,310 --> 00:50:27,770
Do you want a merciless, shit-like war?

521
00:50:29,020 --> 00:50:31,820
A war that unleashes all of nature's fury?

522
00:50:31,900 --> 00:50:37,950
A war like a tempest that kills
all the ravens upon this earth?

523
00:50:41,030 --> 00:50:44,450
<i>Krieg</i>!<i> Krieg</i>!

524
00:50:47,870 --> 00:50:50,830
Then war it is.

525
00:50:51,590 --> 00:50:54,420
We are a clenched fist...

526
00:50:54,510 --> 00:50:58,010
about to be lowered with all its might.

527
00:50:59,010 --> 00:51:05,770
But after enduring over
half a century in the darkness...

528
00:51:05,850 --> 00:51:09,310
for us, a simple, ordinary
war is no longer sufficient.

529
00:51:09,650 --> 00:51:11,650
We need a massive war.

530
00:51:12,150 --> 00:51:15,070
A massive, all-out war!

531
00:51:16,740 --> 00:51:19,360
We are but a single battalion.

532
00:51:19,450 --> 00:51:22,700
The remnants of a defeated army
numbering less than a thousand.

533
00:51:22,780 --> 00:51:26,410
However, I believe that
each of you old warriors

534
00:51:26,500 --> 00:51:28,710
is equal to a thousand of their men.

535
00:51:28,790 --> 00:51:32,040
Which means together, including myself,

536
00:51:32,130 --> 00:51:35,880
we form an army of
one million and one men.

537
00:51:36,210 --> 00:51:37,670
Let's wake them up...

538
00:51:37,760 --> 00:51:42,550
The ones who sent us into oblivion
and who now lie fast asleep.

539
00:51:42,930 --> 00:51:45,140
Let's drag them down by their hair,

540
00:51:45,470 --> 00:51:48,140
open their eyes, and remind them.

541
00:51:48,640 --> 00:51:52,600
Remind them of what
it feels like to live in fear.

542
00:51:52,690 --> 00:51:57,860
Remind them of the sound
of our combat boots!

543
00:52:18,170 --> 00:52:20,510
Remind them that between heaven and hell

544
00:52:20,590 --> 00:52:25,470
there are things they
never thought imaginable.

545
00:52:26,180 --> 00:52:28,930
It's Europe! The light of Europe!

546
00:52:32,560 --> 00:52:35,900
Our<i> Kampfgruppe</i> of a thousand vampires

547
00:52:35,980 --> 00:52:38,280
is going to turn this world to ash.

548
00:52:41,150 --> 00:52:42,650
Yes.

549
00:52:43,320 --> 00:52:47,410
That is the light of Europe
we've been longing for.

550
00:52:53,210 --> 00:52:56,540
I've brought you back
to our old battlefield...

551
00:52:57,290 --> 00:52:59,670
just as I promised.

552
00:52:59,760 --> 00:53:02,260
To our dear beloved war!

553
00:53:02,340 --> 00:53:04,180
Major! Acting Major!

554
00:53:04,260 --> 00:53:06,300
Battalion Commander!

555
00:53:06,390 --> 00:53:08,140
Major! Acting Major...!

556
00:53:13,440 --> 00:53:19,530
At last the sea lion has crossed
the ocean and climbs up upon the land.

557
00:53:22,530 --> 00:53:25,570
To all members of
the Millennium Battalion,

558
00:53:25,660 --> 00:53:28,080
this is an order from your commander.

559
00:53:29,990 --> 00:53:31,700
My friends...

560
00:53:35,540 --> 00:53:38,130
We're going to give them hell.

561
00:55:40,080 --> 00:55:45,590
<i>"At last the sea lion has crossed</i>
<i>the ocean and is heading up the hill."</i>

562
00:56:06,230 --> 00:56:10,240
Subtitle translation by
Charlie Sullivan

